Show HN: User-Space Network Protocol Stack Written in Rust
text:
Hello,

I created a user-space network protocol stack in Rust for study / experiment purpose.

https://github.com/ykskb/rust-user-net

It talks Ethernet / ARP / IP / ICMP / UDP / TCP through TAP device in user space of Linux.

I thought I'd share since it can now successfully send an HTTP request through TCP:80 and receive response till the end.

I hope this would be something of interests for someone :)

Thanks!

title: Show HN - Looking for beta testers/collaborators for www.bookclub.ai
text:
Hi, I am working on this website, www.bookclub.ai It help readers find their next book based on their past preferences. It currently has ML-based recommendation system for 'More Like This' and 'Mind-Map' features.

I am looking for a few beta testers or collaborators who want to work on early-stage product development, community building or training AI models to solve real-life Natural Language Processing & Computer Vision problems in the book industry. Would love to get some critical feedback. If someone is interested, please reach out to me at 19aditiyadav@gmail.com or +1-206-228-4232.
